The Chronicle Andile Tshuma A BULAWAYO architect famed for being one of the designers of the Joshua Mqabuko Nkomo International Airport, Mr Godwin Chitima has died after he was involved in an accident in Woodlands suburb in the wee hours of Wednesday. He was 46. A close family friend, Mr Eddie Chivero confirmed the death. “I can confirm that my longtime friend, Chitima was involved in a car accident and he died on the spot. We are devastated at his sudden passing. He was a young professional with a very good resume and we were all looking forward to greater achievements from him,” said Mr Chivero. Mourners are gathered at his residence in Woodlands. More details to follow…